WEBVTT

00:04.545 --> 00:07.758
Cristina:
DO YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE?

00:09.720 --> 00:11.302
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT'S HAPPENED TO YOU?

00:15.636 --> 00:18.189
DO YOU WANT TO LIVE THIS WAY?

00:20.851 --> 00:22.693
Shane: THERE'S A HOLE
IN THE PERICARDIUM.

00:22.693 --> 00:24.405
THAT'S THE SOURCE
OF ALL THIS BLOOD?

00:24.405 --> 00:26.647
Cristina: NO,
THAT'S WHAT'S KEEPING HIM ALIVE.

00:26.647 --> 00:30.201
[ MONITORS BEEPING ]

00:30.201 --> 00:32.243
WELL, HELLO.

00:32.243 --> 00:36.247
ALL IT TAKES IS ONE PERSON,
ONE PATIENT, ONE MOMENT,

00:36.247 --> 00:38.329
TO CHANGE YOUR LIFE FOREVER.

00:38.329 --> 00:41.041
ROSS, I WOULD LIKE
TO INTRODUCE YOU TO...

00:41.041 --> 00:42.503
THE BLACK MAMBA.

00:42.503 --> 00:46.297
IT CAN CHANGE YOUR PERSPECTIVE,
COLOR YOUR THINKING...

00:46.297 --> 00:48.129
UM...ISN'T THAT THE IVC?

00:48.129 --> 00:51.342
THE SINGLE TRICKIEST VESSEL
IN THE ENTIRE HUMAN BODY --

00:51.342 --> 00:53.304
DELICATE, UNPREDICTABLE.

00:53.304 --> 00:54.595
[ GURGLING ]

00:54.595 --> 00:57.348
HEAR THAT? THE GURGLING?
THAT'S ITS SONG.

00:57.348 --> 00:59.230
SEE THAT?
LOOK HOW IT TWITCHES.

00:59.230 --> 01:03.354
ONE WRONG MOVE, ONE MISSTEP,
AND THIS PATIENT IS DEAD.

01:03.354 --> 01:07.318
YOU CAN'T REPAIR THAT MAMBA
WITHOUT MOVING...

01:07.318 --> 01:08.859
WITH THE MAMBA.
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:08.859 --> 01:11.192
SOME PEOPLE SAY
IT'S IMPOSSIBLE TO REPAIR.

01:11.192 --> 01:12.533
...ONE MOMENT THAT FORCES YOU

01:12.533 --> 01:15.246
TO RE-EVALUATE
EVERYTHING YOU THINK YOU KNOW.

01:15.246 --> 01:16.747
COME ON, MAMBA.

01:16.747 --> 01:18.199
LET'S DANCE.

01:18.199 --> 01:20.331
[ DOOR OPENS ]

01:20.331 --> 01:21.872
YOU PAGED?

01:21.872 --> 01:23.334
MVC VICTIM.

01:23.334 --> 01:26.006
WANTED YOU TO TAKE A LOOK
AT THE C-SPINE X-RAYS.

01:27.338 --> 01:29.420
OH, DAMN.
POOR GUY.

01:29.420 --> 01:31.302
OH. HEY.

01:32.673 --> 01:34.014
I JUST NAILED THE MAMBA.

01:34.014 --> 01:35.346
DO YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE?

01:35.346 --> 01:37.268
THE PATIENT'S C3 AND 4
ARE OBLITERATED.

01:37.268 --> 01:38.389
HIS SPINAL CORD
IS SEVERED.

01:38.389 --> 01:39.930
THERE'S NO WAY
I CAN REPAIR THAT.

01:41.642 --> 01:43.774
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT'S HAPPENED TO YOU?

01:43.774 --> 01:45.726
Shane:
BUT WE JUST FIXED HIS HEART.

01:45.726 --> 01:47.818
AGAINST ALL ODDS.
'CAUSE I'M AWESOME.

01:47.818 --> 01:49.069
YEAH, WELL, EVEN SO,

01:49.069 --> 01:51.532
HE'S LOST ALL MOTOR FUNCTION
FROM THE NECK DOWN.

01:51.532 --> 01:53.904
THE MAN'S PARALYZED.

01:55.576 --> 01:58.118
DO YOU WANT TO LIVE THIS WAY?

01:58.118 --> 02:00.040
[ DOOR OPENS ]

02:01.792 --> 02:03.043
Elise: WAIT. WHAT?

02:03.043 --> 02:05.166
UNFORTUNATELY,
THE IMPACT OF THE CRASH

02:05.166 --> 02:07.298
SEVERED HIS SPINAL CORD
AT C3,

02:07.298 --> 02:09.210
WHICH IS QUITE HIGH
IN THE NECK --

02:09.210 --> 02:11.212
YEAH, NO, I'M A NURSE.
I-I KNOW WHAT C3 IS.

02:11.212 --> 02:13.514
SO YOU'RE SAYING...

02:13.514 --> 02:14.595
HE'S PARALYZED.

02:14.595 --> 02:17.178
YES.

02:17.178 --> 02:19.099
I AM SO SORRY.

02:19.099 --> 02:21.222
BUT HIS BRAIN FUNCTION
IS GOOD,

02:21.222 --> 02:23.724
AND I WAS ABLE
TO FULLY REPAIR HIS HEART --

02:23.724 --> 02:27.318
UH, IS HIS DIAPHRAGM WORKING?
CAN HE BREATHE ON HIS OWN?

02:27.318 --> 02:30.321
NO, HE'S CURRENTLY
ON A VENTILATOR.

02:30.321 --> 02:34.114
THERE ARE OPTIONS FROM HERE,
ONCE HE'S HAD TIME TO RECOVER --

02:34.114 --> 02:37.117
UH, SURGERY TO FUSE HIS SPINE
SO HE CAN SIT UP.

02:37.117 --> 02:39.830
WE CAN, UH, INSERT
A-A PERMANENT TRACH.

02:39.830 --> 02:41.622
THESE ARE ALL OPTIONS
WE CAN DISCUSS --

02:41.622 --> 02:43.584
WILL HE EVER
BREATHE ON HIS OWN AGAIN?

02:45.206 --> 02:46.997
NO. HE WILL NOT.

02:46.997 --> 02:49.920
OKAY, UM...

02:49.920 --> 02:52.923
I NEED YOU TO WAKE HIM UP --
RIGHT NOW.

02:52.923 --> 02:54.255
YOU CAN DO THAT, RIGHT?

02:54.255 --> 02:56.467
ELISE, YOUR HUSBAND
JUST UNDERWENT MAJOR SURGERY.

02:56.467 --> 02:59.430
I KNOW, AND NOW I'M ASKING YOU
TO WAKE HIM UP.

02:59.430 --> 03:01.302
AND I NEED YOU
TO ASK HIM

03:01.302 --> 03:03.354
IF HE WANTS YOU
TO REMOVE THE VENT.

03:03.354 --> 03:05.516
WELL, THE VENT
IS BREATHING FOR HIM.

03:05.516 --> 03:07.187
IT'S -- IT'S WHAT'S
KEEPING HIM ALIVE.

03:07.187 --> 03:08.689
I WAS GONNA SURPRISE HIM
TONIGHT.

03:08.689 --> 03:10.190
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:10.190 --> 03:13.193
AS AN EARLY ANNIVERSARY GIFT,
I GOT US PLAYOFF TICKETS.

03:13.193 --> 03:16.156
I MEAN, NOSEBLEED SEATS,
BUT WE KIND OF LOVE IT UP THERE.

03:16.156 --> 03:18.869
IT'S LIKE, PRETZELS
AND HOT DOGS FOR DINNER.

03:18.869 --> 03:21.121
[ CHUCKLES ]
I MEAN, IT'S FUN.

03:21.121 --> 03:26.086
THE LAST THING I THOUGHT
WHEN I WOKE UP THIS MORNING

03:26.086 --> 03:28.419
WAS I'D LOSE JASON.

03:30.130 --> 03:32.633
I UNDERSTAND...

03:32.633 --> 03:33.754
WHAT I'M ASKING.

03:33.754 --> 03:37.137
BELIEVE ME,
I DON'T WANT TO LOSE HIM.

03:37.137 --> 03:39.430
BUT...[ SIGHS ]

03:39.430 --> 03:43.304
I KNOW HIM.
I KNOW EVERYTHING ABOUT HIM.

03:43.304 --> 03:45.436
I UNDERSTAND HOW HE THINKS.
I GET HIS HUMOR.

03:45.436 --> 03:48.148
I COULD PREDICT WHAT HE'S GONNA
ORDER IN A RESTAURANT.

03:48.148 --> 03:52.853
AND I JUST -- I DON'T THINK
HE WOULD WANT THIS.

03:52.853 --> 03:55.155
I KNOW IT.

03:55.155 --> 03:57.318
I THINK
HE WOULD RATHER DIE

03:57.318 --> 04:00.281
THAN LIVE ONE MORE MINUTE
HOOKED UP TO A MACHINE.

04:00.281 --> 04:03.203
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

04:05.456 --> 04:07.458
IT'S YOUR HUSBAND'S RIGHT
TO DECLINE TREATMENT,

04:07.458 --> 04:09.750
IF THAT'S WHAT HE WANTS.

04:09.750 --> 04:12.172
UH, IT'LL --
IT'LL TAKE SOME TIME

04:12.172 --> 04:14.295
TO FULLY WEAN HIM
OFF THE SEDATION,

04:14.295 --> 04:17.428
BUT I'LL LET YOU KNOW
WHEN HE STARTS TO WAKE.

04:17.428 --> 04:19.880
THANK YOU.

04:19.880 --> 04:21.972
Alex: I THINK
SHE REALLY MEANS IT.

04:21.972 --> 04:23.724
Meredith:
AND THAT BUGS YOU?

04:23.724 --> 04:25.686
NO. I MEAN, MAYBE.
I DON'T KNOW.

04:25.686 --> 04:27.388
IT'S JUST...
I DON'T KNOW.

04:27.388 --> 04:30.561
IT'S NOT LIKE I WANT TO
GET MARRIED TOMORROW, BUT NEVER?

04:30.561 --> 04:32.152
BUT YOU'RE WITH HER.

04:32.152 --> 04:35.195
I-IF YOU LOVE HER, WHO CARES
IF SHE'S NOT THE MARRYING KIND?

04:35.195 --> 04:37.107
I WASN'T.
YEAH,
BUT THEN YOU DID.

04:37.107 --> 04:38.569
RIGHT,
BUT SOME PEOPLE DON'T.

04:38.569 --> 04:40.991
SO, WHAT -- WE JUST KEEP DOING
WHAT WE'RE DOING

04:40.991 --> 04:43.704
FOR THE NEXT 20 YEARS,
AND THAT'S IT?

04:43.704 --> 04:46.907
BUT IF YOU'RE TOGETHER,
WHAT DOES IT MATTER?

04:46.907 --> 04:49.410
[ PAGER CHIMES ]

04:49.410 --> 04:50.461
HEY!

04:50.461 --> 04:51.712
HEY.

04:51.712 --> 04:53.253
DIDN'T SEE YOU THERE.

04:53.253 --> 04:54.545
YOU OKAY?

04:55.626 --> 04:57.217
YEP.

04:57.217 --> 04:58.589
Cristina: JASON?

04:58.589 --> 05:00.551
MY NAME IS DR. YANG.

05:00.551 --> 05:02.723
I KNOW YOU MUST BE
VERY CONFUSED RIGHT NOW,

05:02.723 --> 05:06.266
BUT I NEED TO ASK YOU
SOME QUESTIONS, OKAY?

05:06.266 --> 05:10.020
THERE'S A TUBE DOWN YOUR THROAT,
SO YOU CAN'T SPEAK,

05:10.020 --> 05:12.813
BUT YOU SHOULD BE ABLE
TO NOD "YES" OR "NO."

05:12.813 --> 05:14.234
THINK YOU CAN DO THAT
FOR ME?

05:16.236 --> 05:18.238
THAT'S GREAT.
OKAY. LET'S GET STARTED.

05:18.238 --> 05:20.651
DO YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE?

05:22.823 --> 05:24.865
DO YOU KNOW
WHERE YOU ARE?

05:28.328 --> 05:30.621
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT HAS HAPPENED TO YOU?

05:33.333 --> 05:35.295
YOU WERE
IN A CAR ACCIDENT.

05:35.295 --> 05:37.458
YOUR VEHICLE
WAS HIT FROM BEHIND,

05:37.458 --> 05:40.170
AND YOU FLIPPED OVER
INTO ONCOMING TRAFFIC.

05:40.170 --> 05:41.922
YOU'RE IN A HOSPITAL
RIGHT NOW.

05:44.635 --> 05:46.767
DO YOU KNOW
WHO THIS IS?

05:50.431 --> 05:54.234
YOUR SPINE WAS CRUSHED
IN THE ACCIDENT,

05:54.234 --> 05:57.568
AND YOU ARE PARALYZED
FROM THE NECK DOWN.

05:57.568 --> 06:00.070
YOU'RE CURRENTLY BREATHING
WITH THE HELP OF A VENTILATOR.

06:00.070 --> 06:01.361
THAT'S THE TUBE
IN YOUR MOUTH.

06:01.361 --> 06:04.194
NOW, I UNDERSTAND
IT MIGHT BE YOUR WISH

06:04.194 --> 06:05.866
FOR ME
TO REMOVE THE VENT?

06:10.200 --> 06:13.414
I WANT TO MAKE SURE
YOU UNDERSTAND WHAT THIS MEANS.

06:13.414 --> 06:16.417
THE VENTILATOR
IS BREATHING FOR YOU.

06:18.839 --> 06:20.210
THAT MEANS,
ONCE IT'S REMOVED,

06:20.210 --> 06:22.262
YOU WILL NOT BE ABLE
TO BREATHE ON YOUR OWN.

06:23.804 --> 06:26.887
NOW,
IF YOU CAN'T BREATHE...

06:26.887 --> 06:28.098
YOU WILL DIE.

06:28.098 --> 06:31.181
IT MIGHT TAKE A FEW HOURS --
PROBABLY LESS.

06:32.893 --> 06:34.144
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THIS?

06:36.316 --> 06:37.478
Elise: [ Voice breaking ]
OH, GOD.

06:40.070 --> 06:42.402
DO YOU STILL WANT ME
TO REMOVE THE VENT?

06:45.155 --> 06:47.117
I LOVE YOU.

06:49.029 --> 06:50.330
[ SNIFFLES ]

06:50.330 --> 06:54.294
AND I WANT YOU TO KNOW,
WHATEVER YOU DECIDE...

06:54.294 --> 06:56.126
[ SNIFFLES ]

06:56.126 --> 06:58.879
...I'LL SUPPORT YOU.

06:58.879 --> 07:03.093
I'LL BE BY YOUR SIDE,
NO MATTER WHAT.

07:10.180 --> 07:14.054
I'M SORRY, BUT I HAVE TO ASK
ONE MORE TIME.

07:14.054 --> 07:16.607
JASON...

07:16.607 --> 07:18.609
WOULD YOU LIKE ME
TO REMOVE THE VENT?

07:45.636 --> 07:47.848
DO YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE?

07:57.187 --> 08:00.521
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT'S HAPPENED TO YOU?

08:02.983 --> 08:05.485
DO YOU WANT TO LIVE THIS WAY?

08:08.609 --> 08:09.700
[ CLATTERING ]

08:09.700 --> 08:11.201
OHH! GOD!

08:11.201 --> 08:13.113
HEY, YOU.

08:13.113 --> 08:15.916
WHAT ARE WE DOING?
WHAT THE HELL ARE WE DOING?

08:15.916 --> 08:18.378
I'M...WAITING
FOR AN ELEVATOR?

08:18.378 --> 08:20.210
I JUST SPENT MY DAY

08:20.210 --> 08:22.673
SAVING THE LIFE OF A MAN
WHO'S NOW CHOOSING TO DIE,

08:22.673 --> 08:26.176
AND ALL I KEEP THINKING
IS...

08:26.176 --> 08:30.841
YOU AND I ARE
THROWING SO MUCH AWAY.

08:30.841 --> 08:32.302
WE SHOULD BE TOGETHER.

08:32.302 --> 08:35.185
YOU'RE THE LOVE OF MY LIFE,
AND IT IS STUPID --

08:35.185 --> 08:38.518
JUST STUPID --
FOR US TO KEEP PRETENDING.

08:38.518 --> 08:39.690
I LOVE YOU.

08:39.690 --> 08:43.694
I WANT TO BE WITH YOU --
FOR REAL, FOREVER.

08:43.694 --> 08:45.856
IT'S AS SIMPLE AS THAT.

09:02.332 --> 09:04.004
[ LAUGHING ]

09:04.004 --> 09:06.216
[ BOTH PANTING ]

09:06.216 --> 09:07.668
[ SIGHS ]
THAT'S IT.

09:07.668 --> 09:09.930
WE'VE CHRISTENED
EVERY ROOM IN THIS HOUSE.

09:09.930 --> 09:11.011
YEAH. [ CHUCKLES ]

09:11.011 --> 09:13.133
AND IT'S A PRETTY BIG HOUSE.
MM-HMM.

09:13.133 --> 09:15.345
I THOUGHT I WASN'T GONNA MAKE IT
THROUGH THE GUEST ROOM.

09:15.345 --> 09:17.267
YEAH, BUT YOU RALLIED
AT THE END. MM-HMM.
MM-HMM, I DID.

09:18.979 --> 09:21.521
YOU KNOW, THE HOUSE FEELS BIG
FOR JUST TWO OF US.

09:21.521 --> 09:23.183
DON'T YOU THINK?

09:23.183 --> 09:25.816
[ DOGS BARKING ]

09:27.357 --> 09:29.529
AH. [ CHUCKLES ]
HE IS GORGEOUS.

09:29.529 --> 09:31.782
NO.
OH.

09:31.782 --> 09:33.954
OKAY. UM...

09:33.954 --> 09:35.035
THIS ONE.

09:35.035 --> 09:37.407
I AGREED TO A DOG,
NOT A HORSE.

09:37.407 --> 09:39.289
[ Chuckling ]
THAT'S A MID-SIZE DOG.

09:39.289 --> 09:41.371
NO, THAT IS HUGE.
YOU KNOW WHAT A BIG DOG MAKES?

09:41.371 --> 09:42.833
WHAT?
BIG POOP.

09:42.833 --> 09:46.837
THAT THING COULD CRAP
MY ENTIRE BODY WEIGHT IN A DAY.

09:46.837 --> 09:49.419
HMM. THAT IS A BEAUTIFUL IMAGE.
THANK YOU.

09:49.419 --> 09:51.762
[ GROWLING ]

09:53.714 --> 09:54.885
THAT ONE.

09:54.885 --> 09:56.176
WHAT?
THAT'S THE ONE.

09:56.176 --> 09:58.268
NO. [ Chuckling ] NO.
THAT IS NOT EVEN A DOG.

09:58.268 --> 10:00.891
THAT IS A RODENT,
AND IT LOOKS MEAN.

10:00.891 --> 10:02.933
HEY, UH,
WE WANT THIS THING IN HERE.

10:02.933 --> 10:04.024
CAN SOMEONE GET IT OUT?

10:04.024 --> 10:05.225
Cristina:
CONDUIT, PLEASE.

10:05.225 --> 10:06.606
Shane:
FRESH OFF THE PRINTER.

10:06.606 --> 10:07.938
Alex:
KID'S TINY FOR 12 MONTHS.

10:07.938 --> 10:09.730
HE'LL GROW
WHEN HIS HEART'S SENDING

10:09.730 --> 10:11.191
A LITTLE MORE BLOOD
AROUND THE SYSTEM.

10:11.191 --> 10:12.783
THE FIRST COUPLE KIDS
WE PUT CONDUITS IN,

10:12.783 --> 10:14.785
YOU CAN ALREADY SEE
THE DIFFERENCE IN ONLY A YEAR.

10:14.785 --> 10:17.497
[ SIGHS ] HEY, SO,
I HAVE AN EMERGENCY SURGERY.

10:17.497 --> 10:19.409
I'M GONNA BE IN THE O.R.
FOR THE NEXT NINE HOURS.

10:19.409 --> 10:21.161
OKAY.
MRS. RODRIGUEZ!

10:21.161 --> 10:23.744
OH, NO. THIS IS GONNA TAKE ME
AT LEAST THREE HOURS.

10:23.744 --> 10:25.876
WELL, MRS. RODRIGUEZ
IS NOT GONNA MAKE IT.

10:25.876 --> 10:27.047
IS SHE A CARDIO PATIENT?

10:27.047 --> 10:28.959
I COULD HAVE SOMEBODY
PAGE YOU A CONSULT.

10:28.959 --> 10:31.461
MRS. RODRIGUEZ WILL LAST
UNTIL I FINISH HERE,
AND THEN I'LL GO.

10:31.461 --> 10:33.884
ROSS,
YOU'LL CLOSE FOR ME?
YEAH.

10:33.884 --> 10:35.305
ARE YOU SURE?

10:35.305 --> 10:36.757
WELL, THIS IS WHY I SAID
WE SHOULD KEEP THE DAMN DOG

10:36.757 --> 10:38.098
IN THE KITCHEN
WHEN WE'RE GONE.

10:38.098 --> 10:39.760
I AM NOT LOCKING THE DOG
IN THE KITCHEN.

10:39.760 --> 10:41.892
WELL, THEN YOU CAN CLEAN
UP THE PUDDLE ON THE RUG
WHEN YOU GET HOME.

10:41.892 --> 10:42.723
I'LL LEAVE IT FOR YOU!

10:42.723 --> 10:44.394
YOU GOT A DOG?

10:45.605 --> 10:46.606
YES.

10:46.606 --> 10:47.858
THING'S GONNA BE DEAD
IN A WEEK.

10:47.858 --> 10:50.610
WAIT. YOU NAMED YOUR DOG
MRS. RODRIGUEZ?

10:50.610 --> 10:52.482
WHEN YOU MEET HIM,
YOU'LL UNDERSTAND.

10:52.482 --> 10:54.825
MEET HIM SOON --
BEFORE HE DIES.

10:54.825 --> 10:56.576
WHAT? I'M A PHYSICIAN!

10:56.576 --> 10:58.869
IT'S NOT LIKE I'M GONNA HAVE
TROUBLE KEEPING AN ANIMAL ALIVE.

10:58.869 --> 10:59.870
UH-HUH.

10:59.870 --> 11:01.081
GIVE 5-0 PROLENE,
PLEASE.

11:01.081 --> 11:02.743
WHAT? YOU THINK
I CAN'T KEEP A DOG ALIVE?

11:02.743 --> 11:04.745
WHATEVER.
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
HE'S PERFECTLY HEALTHY.

11:04.745 --> 11:06.877
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

11:06.877 --> 11:08.999
ALEX, IT'S NOT FUNNY.

11:12.052 --> 11:13.343
I CAN'T BELIEVE

11:13.343 --> 11:15.465
YOU'RE GONNA DRESS THE DOG
IN MY SON'S SWEATER.

11:15.465 --> 11:17.968
MRS. RODRIGUEZ GETS COLD.

11:17.968 --> 11:21.351
HE DOESN'T HAVE THE CONSTITUTION
FOR ALL THIS DAMP AND RAIN.

11:21.351 --> 11:22.893
HE GETS THE SHAKES.

11:22.893 --> 11:24.855
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:24.855 --> 11:26.066
WHAT?

11:26.066 --> 11:27.517
YOU LIKE THE DOG!

11:27.517 --> 11:28.899
HE'S AN UNUSUAL DOG.

11:28.899 --> 11:31.441
IT'S NOT LIKE I'M BECOMING
SOMEONE WHO LIKES DOGS.

11:31.441 --> 11:33.984
HE JUST HAPPENS TO
RELATE TO PEOPLE LIKE I DO.

11:33.984 --> 11:35.816
UH-HUH.
IT'S TRUE.

11:35.816 --> 11:37.317
I MEAN,
HE DOESN'T WANT TO TALK

11:37.317 --> 11:38.949
ABOUT HIS FEELINGS
OR THE FUTURE.

11:38.949 --> 11:41.371
IF I WALK HIM AND FEED HIM
ON A REGULAR SCHEDULE,

11:41.371 --> 11:43.243
HE'LL CURL UP NEXT TO ME
ON THE COUCH,

11:43.243 --> 11:45.085
AND IF I DON'T,
HE'LL BITE MY ANKLES.

11:45.085 --> 11:47.287
IT'S A SET OF BEHAVIORS
THAT MAKES SENSE TO ME.

11:47.287 --> 11:48.628
YOU LIKE THE DOG.

11:48.628 --> 11:49.960
THE DOG GETS YOU.

11:49.960 --> 11:51.631
YOU'RE ALIKE.

11:51.631 --> 11:53.293
THAT'S HOW
I TALK ABOUT MY CHILDREN.

11:54.755 --> 11:56.967
You have a baby.
OH!

11:56.967 --> 11:58.048
A DOG BABY.
[ DOG BARKING ]

11:58.048 --> 12:00.140
[ LAUGHS ]
MRS. RODRIGUEZ!

12:02.142 --> 12:04.474
I'M SORRY.
I KNOW HOW PAINFUL IT IS.

12:04.474 --> 12:05.806
I'VE BEEN THROUGH IT
MYSELF,

12:05.806 --> 12:07.898
BUT IT'S BEEN OVER TWO YEARS
SINCE THE INJURY,

12:07.898 --> 12:09.729
AND AT SOME POINT, YOU JUST
HAVE TO SAY ENOUGH IS ENOUGH.

12:09.729 --> 12:11.061
WHAT? NO.
Y-YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHERE --

12:11.061 --> 12:12.813
HEY, LOOK, YOUR HAND
NEEDS MORE TIME, ALL RIGHT?

12:12.813 --> 12:14.905
JUST GIVE YOUR HAND REST,
THROW YOURSELF INTO THE REHAB.

12:14.905 --> 12:17.357
I'VE DONE THE REHAB!
IT'S BEEN TWO YEARS!

12:17.357 --> 12:18.779
IT'S DONE, OKAY?
I'M GOOD ENOUGH TO OPERATE.

12:18.779 --> 12:21.741
I MEAN, WHAT IS THIS?
IS THIS ABOUT MR. WILLENSTEIN?

12:21.741 --> 12:23.954
THAT WAS A ROUTINE --
THE DECISION HAS BEEN MADE.

12:23.954 --> 12:25.996
YOU CAN KEEP
YOUR ADMINISTRATIVE DUTIES,

12:25.996 --> 12:28.038
BUT YOU ARE NOT CLEARED
TO OPERATE.

12:28.038 --> 12:30.460
YOU'RE NOT GOING BACK
IN THE O.R.

12:36.046 --> 12:37.798
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

12:39.880 --> 12:41.802
ANY OTHER BUSINESS
BEFORE WE ADJOURN?

12:41.802 --> 12:44.014
ACTUALLY, UH...
YES, THERE IS.

12:45.725 --> 12:47.727
Cristina: YOU HAD TO BRING IT UP
TO THE BOARD!

12:47.727 --> 12:49.519
YEAH. IT WAS TIME.

12:49.519 --> 12:52.352
IT ABSOLUTELY WAS NOT TIME.
WE DIDN'T MAKE THE DECISION YET.

12:52.352 --> 12:54.524
WELL, CLEARLY, I'M WRONG,
'CAUSE WE DID.

12:54.524 --> 12:56.196
I JUST
WASN'T PART OF IT.

12:56.196 --> 12:58.899
LISTEN, IT IS
THE JOB OF A LIFETIME.

12:58.899 --> 13:01.952
RUNNING THE ENTIRE MILITARY
TRAUMA DIVISION WITH TEDDY --

13:01.952 --> 13:04.034
IT'S -- IT'S WHAT'S NEXT
FOR ME, CRISTINA.

13:04.034 --> 13:05.205
I CAN FEEL IT.

13:05.205 --> 13:06.907
YEAH -- IN GERMANY!

13:06.907 --> 13:09.329
WE HAVE A HOUSE!
I HAVE MY TRIAL!

13:10.871 --> 13:12.752
WE ARE GOOD HERE, OWEN.
WE'RE HAPPY.

13:12.752 --> 13:14.374
WE CAN'T JUST
LEAVE EVERYTHING.

13:14.374 --> 13:15.966
JUST LISTEN TO ME
FOR ONE SECOND --

13:15.966 --> 13:17.087
NO. NO.
YOU WANT TO KNOW WHAT?

13:17.087 --> 13:18.758
YOU'RE NOT
BACKING ME INTO THIS.

13:18.758 --> 13:20.680
[ Chuckling ] COME ON.
NOBODY BACKS YOU INTO ANYTHING.

13:20.680 --> 13:21.842
BELIEVE ME -- I'VE TRIED.

13:21.842 --> 13:23.053
SO, YOU WANT ME TO DUMP
MY WHOLE TRIAL,

13:23.053 --> 13:24.845
JUST WHEN I'M STARTING
TO GET SOMEWH--

13:24.845 --> 13:26.426
THAT IS NOT WHAT I'M SAYI--
PLEASE STOP.

13:26.426 --> 13:28.728
STOP ACTING LIKE
YOU'RE SOME HIT-AND-RUN VICTIM.

13:28.728 --> 13:30.310
I CAN'T HAVE
ANOTHER CONVERSATION

13:30.310 --> 13:32.102
WHERE THE IDEA
THAT MY CAREER

13:32.102 --> 13:35.065
OR, IN FACT, ANY OF MY WISHES
MIGHT COME FIRST

13:35.065 --> 13:38.108
IS PRESENTED AS SOME...
CRIME AGAINST HUMANITY!

13:38.108 --> 13:39.529
OH, WHAT?
[ DOG BARKING ]

13:39.529 --> 13:41.111
SO, NOW WE'RE BACK
WHERE WE STARTED?

13:41.111 --> 13:42.442
I NEVER GIVE YOU ANYTHING,

13:42.442 --> 13:43.864
SO THE TERMS
UNDER WHICH WE'RE TOGETHER

13:43.864 --> 13:45.615
ARE THAT YOUR DREAMS DIE?

13:45.615 --> 13:47.948
[ DOG BARKING ]
[ SIGHS ]
CAN YOU QUIET THE DAMN DOG?

13:47.948 --> 13:49.829
YOU KNOW WHAT? YOU QUIET THE
DAMN DOG. YOU WANTED THE DOG.

13:49.829 --> 13:52.042
NOT THAT DOG! HE DOESN'T EVEN
LIKE ME. HE ONLY LIKES YOU.

13:52.042 --> 13:54.875
BECAUSE YOU MAKE STUPID
DECISIONS! AND HE KNOWS IT!

13:54.875 --> 13:57.257
I'M NOT MOVING
TO GERMANY!

13:57.257 --> 13:58.718
[ SCOFFS ]

13:58.718 --> 14:00.510
OH, SO, THAT'S IT?
CONVERSATION'S OVER?

14:00.510 --> 14:01.511
UH-HUH.

14:01.511 --> 14:02.762
OF COURSE IT IS.

14:02.762 --> 14:04.014
[ BARKING CONTINUES ]

14:04.014 --> 14:05.015
[ SIGHS ]

14:05.015 --> 14:06.136
I DON'T KNOW WHY

14:06.136 --> 14:07.807
I EVER ENTERTAINED THE IDEA
FOR ONE SECOND

14:07.807 --> 14:10.600
THAT WE MIGHT EVER DO
ANYTHING THAT I'D WANT.

14:10.600 --> 14:11.771
[ BARKING CONTINUES ]

14:16.146 --> 14:16.937
Shh!

14:16.937 --> 14:18.939
[ WHIMPERS ]

14:18.939 --> 14:20.360
COMING THROUGH!
DR. YANG!

14:20.360 --> 14:22.362
OH, WHATEVER IT IS,
IT CAN WAIT.

14:22.362 --> 14:24.364
MY SHIFT IS OVER,
AND I AM GOING HOME.

14:24.364 --> 14:26.196
COME ON.
PATIENT 11 -- JASPER O'NEIL.

14:26.196 --> 14:27.867
HE'S BACK
FOR HIS ANNUAL CHECKUP.

14:27.867 --> 14:29.910
APPARENTLY,
HE'S LEARNING TO PLAY HOCKEY.

14:29.910 --> 14:31.831
YOU HANDLE IT.
SEND HIM MY BEST.

14:31.831 --> 14:33.663
BUT IF MY CONDUIT
GETS SMASHED

14:33.663 --> 14:36.296
BECAUSE THEY LET THEIR KID
GET BODY-CHECKED ON THE ICE,

14:36.296 --> 14:37.297
I'M KILLING THEM!

14:37.297 --> 14:38.298
WILL DO.

14:38.298 --> 14:39.669
[ Chuckling ]
OH! HI!

14:39.669 --> 14:40.800
HEY,
WHO'D HAVE THUNK IT?

14:40.800 --> 14:42.923
YOU AND ME --
WE'RE BELLY BUDDIES.

14:42.923 --> 14:44.554
NO, WE'RE NOT.

14:50.510 --> 14:51.431
[ SCREAMING ]

14:51.431 --> 14:53.063
IT'S OKAY.
YOU'RE ALMOST THERE.

14:53.063 --> 14:54.314
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS PUSH.

14:54.314 --> 14:55.855
NO. NO CAN DO.

14:55.855 --> 14:57.437
WE ARE ALMOST THERE.
HE'S GONNA
HAVE TO STAY UP IN THERE.

14:57.437 --> 14:59.729
I'VE GOT A COZY WOMB.
HE'LL BE HAPPIER.

14:59.729 --> 15:01.731
IT'LL BE BETTER
FOR EVERYONE.

15:01.731 --> 15:03.783
OH, MY GOD! OH, GOD!
OH, GOD!
WHOA, WHOA. WAIT A SECOND.

15:03.783 --> 15:05.485
YOU HAVE TO WAIT
A SECOND.
NO, I CAN'T!

15:05.485 --> 15:07.157
YOU HAVE TO WAIT
ONE SECOND.
I CAN'T, I CAN'T.

15:07.157 --> 15:09.409
OH, GOD. THIS IS A MISTAKE.
IT'S A MISTAKE!

15:09.409 --> 15:11.081
[ Crying ]
I CAN'T! I CAN'T!
WHAT?

15:11.081 --> 15:13.413
THIS IS A MISTAKE, MER!
EVERYONE SAYS THAT.

15:13.413 --> 15:15.455
Obstetrician: HERE WE GO.
WE NEED ONE MORE PUSH.
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

15:15.455 --> 15:16.496
OKAY, NOW!

15:16.496 --> 15:20.210
PUSH! PUSH! PUSH!
[ GRUNTING ]

15:20.210 --> 15:22.842
[ WAILING ]

15:22.842 --> 15:24.844
GREAT!
[ BABY CRYING ]

15:29.139 --> 15:30.550
[ GASPS ]

15:45.235 --> 15:47.867
I SCREWED UP, MER.

15:47.867 --> 15:51.411
MER, I SCREWED UP.
I REALLY SCREWED UP.

15:51.411 --> 15:53.493
Shh.

15:53.493 --> 15:55.285
[ Crying ] I CAN'T --

15:59.539 --> 16:03.503
[ MURMURING ]

16:03.503 --> 16:05.295
OH...

16:06.796 --> 16:08.428
HELLO.

16:08.428 --> 16:09.799
[ CRYING ]

16:09.799 --> 16:12.092
[ GRUNTS ]

16:12.092 --> 16:15.095
OH. GO BACK TO SLEEP.
I GOT THIS.

16:15.095 --> 16:16.516
OKAY.

16:22.522 --> 16:25.525
[ CRYING CONTINUES ]

16:48.007 --> 16:51.010
[ CRYING CONTINUES ]

16:53.303 --> 16:56.056
IT'S OKAY.
YOU'RE DOING GOOD.
YOU'RE BEING SO GOOD.

16:56.056 --> 16:57.557
YEAH.
HE'S FINE. HE'S FINE.

16:57.557 --> 17:00.310
[ BABY CRYING ]

17:00.310 --> 17:02.852
THIS IS ALL MY FAULT. YOU KNOW,
I WAS -- I WAS AT THE PARK,

17:02.852 --> 17:05.235
AND I LOOKED AWAY FOR A SECOND
WHEN ROSS TEXTED ME.

17:05.235 --> 17:06.906
I WAS -- I WAS STANDING
RIGHT THERE.

17:06.906 --> 17:08.778
LISTEN, IT'S OKAY.
THESE THINGS HAPPEN.

17:08.778 --> 17:10.280
AND HAVE YOU MET
OUR SON?

17:10.280 --> 17:11.821
HE LUNGES HEADFIRST
INTO EVERYTHING.

17:11.821 --> 17:13.363
IT'S A WONDER
THIS NEVER HAPPENED SOONER.

17:13.363 --> 17:14.954
WELL, WE CAN'T GO BACK
TO THAT PARK.

17:14.954 --> 17:17.367
THEY NEED, LIKE, SAND
OR SOME OF THAT SOFT TURF STUFF.

17:17.367 --> 17:19.659
I MEAN, WHO PUTS CONCRETE STEPS
BY A PLAY SPACE?

17:19.659 --> 17:21.000
IT'S COMPLETELY
IRRESPONSIBLE.

17:21.000 --> 17:22.792
IT IS A SUPERFICIAL CUT.
HE'S GONNA BE FINE.

17:22.792 --> 17:24.374
I'M ALREADY LATE
FOR MY MEETING.

17:24.374 --> 17:26.376
I CAN'T JUST --
I CAN'T JUST STICK HIM
IN DAYCARE, NOT WHEN --

17:26.376 --> 17:29.008
SLOW DOWN.
SLOW DOWN, OKAY?

17:29.008 --> 17:31.050
NOW, WE'RE GONNA
FIGURE THIS OUT.

17:31.050 --> 17:34.344
AND, BY THE WAY, DAYCARE HAS
VERY CAPABLE TEACHERS.

17:34.344 --> 17:36.556
OH, PLEASE.
I AM CAPABLE.

17:36.556 --> 17:39.389
SO, YOUR TEXT SAID "MAKE SURE
THE PHASE 3 PATIENTS GO."

17:39.389 --> 17:41.391
GO TO THE BATHROOM?
GO AWAY?

17:41.391 --> 17:43.483
OH. SORRY. I DIDN'T REALIZE.
IS HE OKAY?

17:43.483 --> 17:44.524
YES.
NO.

17:44.524 --> 17:45.775
UH, DO YOU WANT ME
TO RESCHEDULE

17:45.775 --> 17:46.946
THE PHASE 3 PATIENT MEETINGS
TODAY,

17:46.946 --> 17:48.148
MAYBE TRY TO SQUEEZE THEM IN
NEXT WEEK, OR --

17:48.148 --> 17:50.490
NO, JUST, UM...

17:50.490 --> 17:52.782
ROSS, WILL YOU TAKE THEM?
YOU UNDERSTAND THE PROCEDURE.

17:52.782 --> 17:54.284
YOU KNOW WHAT TO DO.
JUST -- I --

17:54.284 --> 17:56.366
YOU KNOW, I WANT YOU
TO TAKE OVER PHASE 3 FROM HERE.

17:56.366 --> 17:57.407
WHAT?

17:57.407 --> 17:58.828
WHAT -- ARE YOU SURE?

17:58.828 --> 18:01.501
YES. CAN YOU DO THIS FOR ME?
JUST DO THIS FOR ME, OKAY?

18:01.501 --> 18:04.504
OF COURSE,
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT.

18:04.504 --> 18:06.506
[ BABY CRYING ]

18:08.708 --> 18:12.302
[ CHILDREN SCREAMING, LAUGHING ]

18:12.302 --> 18:15.054
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

18:17.056 --> 18:20.270
I CAN'T BELIEVE
BAILEY'S ALREADY 7.

18:20.270 --> 18:22.522
PLEASE TELL ME
HE HAS OUTGROWN THAT WHOLE

18:22.522 --> 18:25.435
"I FIDDLE WITH MY JUNK 24/7"
PHASE,

18:25.435 --> 18:27.527
'CAUSE I HAVE TO PRACTICALLY
DUCT-TAPE THEO'S PANTS

18:27.527 --> 18:29.609
ON HIS BODY.
[ LAUGHS ]

18:29.609 --> 18:33.323
OF ALL THE CONVERSATIONS THAT
YOU AND I HAVE HAD ABOUT BOYS,

18:33.323 --> 18:35.535
I DIDN'T EXPECT THIS ONE
TO BE IT.

18:35.535 --> 18:36.946
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

18:38.538 --> 18:40.540
[ LAUGHS ]

18:40.540 --> 18:42.242
FEEL ANY KICKS YET?

18:42.242 --> 18:44.414
UH, NO, NOT REALLY.

18:46.045 --> 18:47.167
NAUSEOUS?

18:47.167 --> 18:48.418
OH, JUST TIRED.

18:51.090 --> 18:54.924
EVERY DAY, I GO TO WORK
AND DO MY JOB.

18:54.924 --> 18:56.886
THEN I COME HOME
AND DO THAT JOB.

18:56.886 --> 18:59.889
I'M SO TIRED.

18:59.889 --> 19:02.522
IT'S LIKE I'M SLEEPWALKING
ALL THE TIME.

19:02.522 --> 19:05.104
WELL, YOU'RE WELL INTO
YOUR SECOND TRIMESTER NOW,

19:05.104 --> 19:06.976
SO THAT'LL START
GETTING BETTER.

19:06.976 --> 19:09.359
IT'S NOT THE PREGNANCY.

19:10.320 --> 19:11.941
CRISTINA...

19:11.941 --> 19:15.034
LOOK HOW HAPPY HE IS.

19:24.454 --> 19:27.247
YOU'RE NOT DRESSED?

19:27.247 --> 19:29.459
WE NEED TO GET GOING.

19:29.459 --> 19:32.552
THE HARPER AVERY AWARDS
AWAIT.

19:32.552 --> 19:35.885
ARE YOU...NERVOUS?

19:35.885 --> 19:37.006
ARE YOU OKAY?

19:37.006 --> 19:38.348
DO YOU NEED A MINUTE?

19:38.348 --> 19:40.300
NO.

19:40.300 --> 19:41.351
MAYBE.

19:41.351 --> 19:43.102
OKAY.

19:43.102 --> 19:44.474
BUT JUST A MINUTE.

19:44.474 --> 19:46.516
AND THEN
NERVES OF STEEL.

19:46.516 --> 19:48.017
RIGHT?

19:48.017 --> 19:49.108
RIGHT.

19:49.108 --> 19:50.109
OKAY.

19:52.312 --> 19:55.905
Cristina: THE SURGICAL MIND
NEEDS TO BE CONSTANTLY INSPIRED,

19:55.905 --> 19:58.448
ALWAYS ASKING
THE TOUGHEST QUESTIONS.

19:58.448 --> 20:02.872
THE HARPER AVERY AWARD
IS A CELEBRATION OF THAT,

20:02.872 --> 20:07.417
OF THE KIND OF MIND I SAW
IN TONIGHT'S RECIPIENT,

20:07.417 --> 20:10.330
EVEN WHEN HE WAS JUST AN INTERN.

20:10.330 --> 20:13.753
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
I AM HONORED TO PRESENT TO YOU

20:13.753 --> 20:16.426
THIS YEAR'S
HARPER AVERY AWARD RECIPIENT

20:16.426 --> 20:17.967
TO DR. SHANE ROSS.

20:21.100 --> 20:23.182
[ CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING ]

20:29.309 --> 20:32.732
THANK YOU.
THANK YOU.

20:32.732 --> 20:35.985
FIRST AND FOREMOST,
I'D LIKE TO THANK DR. YANG.

20:35.985 --> 20:37.357
I WOULDN'T BE HERE

20:37.357 --> 20:41.411
WITHOUT YOUR GUIDANCE,
ENCOURAGEMENT, AND SUPPORT.

20:43.122 --> 20:46.576
ALL IT TAKES IS ONE PERSON,
ONE PATIENT

20:46.576 --> 20:50.710
TO CHANGE YOUR LIFE FOREVER.

20:50.710 --> 20:53.543
WHEN I FIRST MET JASPER O'NEIL,
HE WAS 12 MONTHS OLD,

20:53.543 --> 20:57.006
AND WE DIDN'T THINK
HE'D MAKE IT TO 13.

20:57.006 --> 20:58.548
HE'S HERE WITH US TONIGHT.

20:58.548 --> 21:00.930
JASPER,
WOULD YOU STAND UP, PLEASE?

21:09.148 --> 21:12.151
Meredith:
CRISTINA. CRISTINA.

21:12.151 --> 21:15.985
DO YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE?

21:15.985 --> 21:19.989
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT'S HAPPENED TO YOU?

21:19.989 --> 21:22.071
DO YOU WANT TO LIVE THIS WAY?

21:22.071 --> 21:23.363
Elise: I LOVE YOU.

21:23.363 --> 21:24.704
[ VENTILATOR HISSING ]

21:24.704 --> 21:29.459
AND I WANT YOU TO KNOW
THAT WHATEVER YOU DECIDE...

21:29.459 --> 21:32.622
[ SNIFFLES ]
...I'LL SUPPORT YOU.

21:32.622 --> 21:34.334
I'LL BE BY YOUR SIDE...

21:34.334 --> 21:37.507
NO MATTER WHAT.

21:38.508 --> 21:42.382
I'M SORRY, BUT I HAVE TO ASK
ONE MORE TIME.

21:42.382 --> 21:44.884
JASON...

21:44.884 --> 21:47.266
WOULD YOU LIKE ME
TO REMOVE THE VENT?

22:25.134 --> 22:26.466
[ CLATTERING ]

22:26.466 --> 22:28.137
AAH!

22:28.137 --> 22:29.599
SON OF A --

22:29.599 --> 22:30.810
HEY, YOU.

22:30.810 --> 22:33.563
I JUST SPENT MY DAY
SAVING THE LIFE OF A MAN

22:33.563 --> 22:35.645
WHO COULD'VE CHOSEN TO DIE
BUT DIDN'T.

22:35.645 --> 22:40.069
I REPAIRED A HEART
THAT WAS IMPOSSIBLE TO REPAIR.

22:40.069 --> 22:45.284
I ACHIEVED THE IMPOSSIBLE TODAY,
AND IT FEELS GOOD.

22:45.284 --> 22:47.246
NO. MORE.

22:47.246 --> 22:49.829
IT FEELS...INCREDIBLE.

22:51.491 --> 22:53.332
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
RIGHT NOW?

22:53.332 --> 22:56.456
UM...
WAITING FOR THE ELEVATOR.

22:56.456 --> 22:57.797
YEAH.

22:57.797 --> 22:59.549
WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO TAKE THE STAIRS,

22:59.549 --> 23:00.840
'CAUSE I JUST
FINISHED MY SHIFT,

23:00.840 --> 23:02.341
AND I FEEL LIKE
CELEBRATING...

23:02.341 --> 23:03.963
TONIGHT...

23:03.963 --> 23:05.505
NAKED...

23:05.505 --> 23:06.345
WITH YOU.

23:06.345 --> 23:08.678
OH.
I COULD BE INTO THAT.

23:14.434 --> 23:16.275
[ BOTH CHUCKLING ]

23:22.401 --> 23:24.824
ARE YOU...

23:24.824 --> 23:26.786
SURE YOU'RE OKAY
WITH THIS?

23:26.786 --> 23:29.869
[ OWL HOOTING ]

23:29.869 --> 23:32.241
OH, YEAH, YEAH.
I'M VERY SURE.

23:32.241 --> 23:33.292
[ CHUCKLES ]
NO, NO.

23:33.292 --> 23:36.956
NO, NOT -- NOT THIS.

23:36.956 --> 23:39.038
US...

23:39.038 --> 23:41.751
BEING...

23:41.751 --> 23:43.963
JUST US.

23:45.845 --> 23:47.967
I KNOW.

23:47.967 --> 23:50.099
AND I'M GOOD.

23:50.099 --> 23:51.310
I AM.

23:53.763 --> 23:56.185
YOU SAID YOU WERE OKAY.
YOU TOLD ME --
YEAH, I KNOW.

23:56.185 --> 23:58.978
YOU TOLD ME THAT --
I THOUGHT I WAS, OKAY?
BUT I -- I'M NOT.

23:58.978 --> 24:01.270
WHAT DOES THAT --
I JUST NEED MY FILMS.

24:01.270 --> 24:03.863
[ SIGHS ]
NOT RIGHT THIS SECOND, THOUGH.

24:05.905 --> 24:08.908
LISTEN, ALL I AM ASKING

24:08.908 --> 24:11.621
IS THAT WE JUST REOPEN
THIS CONVERSATION --
NO. NO!

24:11.621 --> 24:13.162
THERE IS NOTHING LEFT
TO TALK ABOUT.

24:13.162 --> 24:14.624
OWEN, I WAS CLEAR
ABOUT THIS.

24:14.624 --> 24:16.035
I WAS SO CLEAR.

24:16.035 --> 24:18.167
I CAN'T GIVE YOU MORE
THAN WHAT I AM ALREADY GIVING,

24:18.167 --> 24:19.839
AND IF NOW YOU NEED MORE --

24:19.839 --> 24:21.751
YES, I THINK I DO!
I THINK I DO!
IF NOW --

24:21.751 --> 24:23.422
WELL, THEN -- THEN GET IT
SOMEWHERE ELSE.

24:25.845 --> 24:27.466
OH.

24:29.759 --> 24:30.800
OKAY, I WILL.

24:33.222 --> 24:34.894
[ DOOR OPENS ]

24:38.978 --> 24:40.690
[ PANTING ]

24:40.690 --> 24:42.902
Cristina:
IT'S -- IT'S OVER.

24:42.902 --> 24:45.484
NO, THIS TIME, OWEN
AND I ARE REALLY OVER.

24:45.484 --> 24:48.908
I MEAN, WE CAN'T KEEP FALLING
BACK INTO THE SAME PATTERN.

24:48.908 --> 24:51.701
IT'S JUST...

24:51.701 --> 24:54.744
MER?
YOU AWAKE?

24:54.744 --> 24:58.538
YEAH. YOU AND OWEN
ARE OVER AGAIN.

24:58.538 --> 25:00.249
I'M TOTALLY LISTENING.
CONTINUE.

25:00.249 --> 25:01.921
WELL, SEE?
THAT'S THE POINT --

25:01.921 --> 25:03.753
I-IT CAN'T CONTINUE
THE WAY IT IS.

25:03.753 --> 25:05.925
IT'S -- IT'S NOT GOOD,
IT'S NOT HEALTHY.

25:05.925 --> 25:07.927
Cristina:
YOUR HEART'S HEALTHY ENOUGH NOW

25:07.927 --> 25:09.969
THAT YOU'D BE
AN EXCELLENT CANDIDATE

25:09.969 --> 25:12.842
FOR THE TYPE
OF RESEARCH THEY'RE DOING.
MM-HMM.

25:12.842 --> 25:13.803
COULD IT HURT HIM?

25:13.803 --> 25:15.394
NO.
IT IS A SURGERY.

25:15.394 --> 25:17.977
I WOULD IMPLANT AN ARRAY OF
WIRELESS SENSORS INTO HIS SKULL

25:17.977 --> 25:19.939
THAT WOULD TRANSMIT
ELECTRICAL ACTIVITY.

25:19.939 --> 25:22.101
BUT NONE OF OUR SUBJECTS
EVER COMPLAINED OF PAIN.

25:22.101 --> 25:24.103
IT'S A CHANCE TO HELP US,
TO HELP REVOLUTIONIZE TREATMENT

25:24.103 --> 25:26.485
FOR PEOPLE LIKE YOURSELF.
HMM?

25:26.485 --> 25:27.526
WHAT DO YOU THINK, HON?

25:27.526 --> 25:30.319
[ VENTILATOR HISSING ]

25:30.319 --> 25:33.703
IT'LL HELP PEOPLE --
"PEOPLE LIKE ME"...

25:33.703 --> 25:35.785
IT WON'T HELP ME?

25:35.785 --> 25:38.287
HONEY, WOULDN'T IT BE NICE
TO HAVE A PLACE TO GO

25:38.287 --> 25:40.539
INSTEAD OF SITTING
AROUND THE HOUSE ALL DAY?

25:40.539 --> 25:43.873
IT'S SOMETHING, JASON.
IT'S SOMETHING WE CAN DO.

25:43.873 --> 25:45.755
PLEASE?

25:45.755 --> 25:47.336
[ VENTILATOR HISSING ]

25:47.336 --> 25:49.088
I DON'T CARE.

25:49.088 --> 25:50.549
FINE.

25:56.435 --> 25:59.178
UM, THANK YOU, DR. YANG,
FOR THINKING OF US.

25:59.178 --> 26:01.560
OH, NO, ACTUALLY,
IT WAS CHIEF HUNT'S IDEA.

26:01.560 --> 26:03.943
HE -- HE TOLD US ABOUT JASON.
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:03.943 --> 26:05.024
[ OWEN CLEARS THROAT ]

26:05.024 --> 26:06.986
Elise: OH, WELL,
THANK YOU, DR. HUNT.

26:06.986 --> 26:08.688
IT'S GONNA BE GREAT FOR HIM.

26:08.688 --> 26:09.949
WELL, GOOD LUCK.

26:13.783 --> 26:15.034
WHAT?

26:15.034 --> 26:17.076
THAT WAS A REALLY NICE THING
YOU DID FOR THEM.

26:17.076 --> 26:18.698
OH, WELL...
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:18.698 --> 26:21.080
I'M A REALLY NICE GUY,
OR SO I'VE BEEN TOLD.

26:21.080 --> 26:22.461
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:22.461 --> 26:24.754
Cristina: I WOULD NEVER
ASK YOU FOR THAT.

26:24.754 --> 26:28.377
YOU'RE NOT ASKING.
I AM TELLING YOU.
WELL...

26:28.377 --> 26:30.339
I DON'T BELIEVE YOU.

26:30.339 --> 26:32.922
[ SIGHS ]
CRISTINA, PEOPLE CHANGE.

26:32.922 --> 26:35.845
I MEAN, YOU'RE NOT
THE SAME PERSON THAT
YOU WERE WHEN WE MET.

26:35.845 --> 26:36.886
I CAN CHANGE, TOO.

26:36.886 --> 26:39.719
REALLY?

26:39.719 --> 26:43.893
PEOPLE WHO WANT KIDS
DON'T JUST STOP WANTING THEM.

26:46.896 --> 26:48.187
DON'T GIVE UP THINGS FOR ME.

26:48.187 --> 26:51.070
HEY, I'M NOT.

26:51.070 --> 26:52.902
I HAVEN'T.

26:55.284 --> 26:57.286
I'M NOT GIVING UP ANYTHING.

27:03.002 --> 27:04.914
Callie: GOOD.
[ MOTORS WHIRRING ]

27:04.914 --> 27:07.416
GOOD. GOOD.

27:07.416 --> 27:09.338
YEAH, SLOWLY BUT SURELY.

27:09.338 --> 27:12.712
JUST FOCUS ON YOUR BALANCE.

27:12.712 --> 27:16.886
HOW DOES IT FEEL,
JASE, TO WALK AGAIN?

27:16.886 --> 27:18.888
IT'S...

27:18.888 --> 27:20.019
PRETTY GOOD.

27:20.019 --> 27:21.891
YEAH, I THINK HE NEEDS
TO CONCENTRATE.

27:24.814 --> 27:28.067
IT'S AMAZING,
IN JUST A FEW YEARS?

27:28.067 --> 27:30.109
UNBELIEVABLE.
[ CHUCKLES, SNIFFLES ]

27:30.109 --> 27:32.942
IS DR. YANG BUSY? I WOULD LOVE
FOR HER TO SEE THIS.
I CAN CHECK, OKAY?

27:32.942 --> 27:34.774
JASON, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

27:36.575 --> 27:37.867
[ GASPS ]
JASON!

27:39.578 --> 27:41.580
Owen:
GET A CRASH CART!
Derek: JASON?

27:43.452 --> 27:46.836
[ MOTOR WHIRRING ]

27:46.836 --> 27:47.917
HEY, I NEED YOU.

27:47.917 --> 27:49.338
YES.

27:49.338 --> 27:50.840
UH, NO. I CAN'T.

27:50.840 --> 27:52.962
UH, THESE ABSTRACTS WERE
SUPPOSED TO GO OUT AN HOUR AGO.

27:52.962 --> 27:55.294
YOU KNOW WHAT? OKAY.
ON-CALL ROOM, BUT FAST?

27:55.294 --> 27:57.256
NO, NO, IT'S NOT, UM --
IT'S JASON CASTOR.

27:57.256 --> 27:59.098
HE JUST HAD AN ACCIDENT
IN THE BCI LAB.

27:59.098 --> 28:01.350
HE HAS RHABDO, RENAL FAILURE.

28:01.350 --> 28:04.143
GREY IS PUTTING A SHUNT IN HIM,
BUT HIS WIFE'S ASKING FOR YOU.

28:06.265 --> 28:08.938
JASON CASTOR -- YOUR PATIENT,
THE QUADRIPLEGIC?

28:08.938 --> 28:10.900
WE, UH, PUT HIM INTO DEREK
AND CALLIE'S TRIAL.

28:10.900 --> 28:13.442
HIS WIFE IS --
OH! RIGHT, RIGHT, RIGHT.
YES. UM...

28:13.442 --> 28:14.864
DOES HE NEED A HEART CONSULT?

28:14.864 --> 28:16.986
NO, NO. SHE'S JUST SCARED,
AND SHE TRUSTS YOU --

28:16.986 --> 28:18.948
YOU KNOW, OWEN, I-I HAVE
TO FINISH THIS.

28:18.948 --> 28:20.369
I'VE GOT SEVEN PRINTS GOING.

28:20.369 --> 28:22.081
WHERE -- WHERE'S ROSS?

28:22.081 --> 28:23.412
ROSS CAN'T DO THIS.

28:23.412 --> 28:26.125
I'M ONE STEP AWAY FROM FUNDING
FOR ANIMAL TRIALS.

28:27.747 --> 28:29.538
OWEN, HE'S NOT MY PATIENT
ANYMORE.

28:29.538 --> 28:30.960
IF THE GUY'S HEART IS FINE,

28:30.960 --> 28:33.502
I DON'T HAVE TIME TO HOLD
SOMEONE'S HAND RIGHT NOW.

28:38.968 --> 28:41.300
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU SAVED HER HUSBAND'S LIFE.

28:41.300 --> 28:42.892
YOU WERE THE FIRST DOCTOR
SHE MET.

28:42.892 --> 28:45.805
SHE LIKES YOU, SHE TRUSTS YOU,
AND NOW SHE'S WAITING FOR YOU.

28:45.805 --> 28:48.227
ABOUT A MILLION HEART PATIENTS
ARE WAITING FOR ME, TOO.

28:49.849 --> 28:51.811
RIGHT.

28:51.811 --> 28:53.732
YOU CAN'T LET PEOPLE DOWN.
[ SIGHS ]

28:53.732 --> 28:55.985
[ DOOR OPENS ]

28:59.859 --> 29:01.911
Owen: HEY.

29:01.911 --> 29:03.742
[ Chuckling ]
OH.

29:03.742 --> 29:05.364
THANKS.

29:05.364 --> 29:07.456
UM, WAS IT BECAUSE
OF THE SUIT?

29:07.456 --> 29:10.709
NO. HIS KIDNEYS FAILED,
AND THAT CAUSED HIM TO PASS OUT.

29:10.709 --> 29:12.461
BUT THE SURGERY
IS GOING WELL,

29:12.461 --> 29:14.834
AND THEN WE'LL GET HIM
ON DIALYSIS.

29:14.834 --> 29:20.219
THIS IS JUST A COMPLICATION
OF JASON'S...CONDITION.

29:20.219 --> 29:22.511
IT'S ALL JUST COMPLICATIONS.

29:22.511 --> 29:25.344
AND HE SHOULD BE ABLE TO
CONTINUE WITH THE STUDY, SO --

29:25.344 --> 29:26.555
HE WON'T.

29:28.557 --> 29:30.269
YEAH, THIS --
THIS WILL BE HIS EXCUSE,

29:30.269 --> 29:32.521
AND HE'LL NEVER FORGIVE ME
FOR MAKING HIM DO IT.

29:32.521 --> 29:35.314
[ SCOFFS ] WHAT?
YOU DIDN'T MAKE HIM DO THIS.

29:35.314 --> 29:37.486
HE TOLD ME ONCE --
W-WE WERE FIGHTING,

29:37.486 --> 29:39.899
AND HE TOLD ME
THAT WHEN WE WOKE HIM

29:39.899 --> 29:42.531
TO ASK HIM
IF HE WANTED TO LIVE,

29:42.531 --> 29:46.205
HE ONLY SAID YES
BECAUSE HE WAS LOOKING AT ME --

29:46.205 --> 29:49.118
THAT IF IT HAD BEEN
UP TO HIM...

29:49.118 --> 29:51.210
IF I WASN'T THERE...

29:51.210 --> 29:53.412
HE WOULD HAVE SAID NO.

29:55.544 --> 29:56.966
SO ALL THIS
IS BECAUSE OF ME.

29:56.966 --> 29:59.178
I MEAN, HE -- HE'S MISERABLE
EVERY DAY BECAUSE OF ME.

29:59.178 --> 30:01.260
AND I-I'M -- I'M -- I'M --
I'M NOT A WIFE ANYMORE.

30:01.260 --> 30:04.183
I'M A NURSEMAID
AND A COOK AND AN ORDERLY,

30:04.183 --> 30:06.555
AND I NEVER GO HOME
FROM THAT WORK.

30:06.555 --> 30:10.189
I AM THAT WORK.
THAT'S ALL I AM ANYMORE.

30:15.274 --> 30:16.936
I WANTED TO HAVE A CHILD.

30:20.239 --> 30:23.402
AND I WILL NEVER,
EVER HAVE A CHILD.

30:26.035 --> 30:28.117
[ Crying ] I'M SORRY.

30:28.117 --> 30:29.538
I'M BEING SELFISH.
I'M HORRIBLE.

30:29.538 --> 30:30.579
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

30:30.579 --> 30:32.371
NO, NO, NO, NO.
NOT AT ALL.

30:32.371 --> 30:34.583
NOT AT ALL.
I-I TOTALLY UNDERSTAND.

30:38.757 --> 30:43.842
MM --

30:43.842 --> 30:45.965
UH --

30:45.965 --> 30:48.347
I'M SORRY.
I'M SO SORRY.

30:48.347 --> 30:51.100
MNH-MNH. NO.
IT'S OKAY.

30:51.100 --> 30:54.523
GET ON OUT! HA!
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

30:54.523 --> 30:56.855
OKAY, NOW, THAT
IS A HEALTHY HEART SIP

30:56.855 --> 30:59.398
THAT'S BOTH DELICIOUS
AND NUTRITIOUS.

30:59.398 --> 31:01.941
[ Laughing ]
THANK YOU VERY MUCH FOR THAT.

31:01.941 --> 31:06.745
NEXT UP, I'M GOING TO DEBUNK
THE TOP FIVE

31:06.745 --> 31:08.407
BIGGEST HEALTH MYTHS
FOR YOU FOLKS,

31:08.407 --> 31:10.539
COMING UP RIGHT AFTER THIS.
[ APPLAUSE ]

31:10.539 --> 31:13.702
SHE BETTER INCLUDE MY SUGGESTION
ON TOO MUCH CALCIUM

31:13.702 --> 31:16.415
INCREASING YOUR RISK
OF HEART DISEASE.

31:16.415 --> 31:18.627
PEOPLE POP THOSE PILLS
LIKE CANDY.

31:20.209 --> 31:22.341
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

31:22.341 --> 31:24.003
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
IN TWO DAYS.

31:24.003 --> 31:26.265
YEAH, I TOOK A COUPLE EXTRA
NIGHT SHIFTS.

31:26.265 --> 31:28.267
I-I WENT BY THE TRAILER
THIS MORNING.

31:28.267 --> 31:30.429
YEAH, I JUST CRASHED
IN THE ON-CALL ROOM.

31:35.774 --> 31:37.516
IS SOMETHING GOING ON?

31:37.516 --> 31:39.518
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:45.364 --> 31:48.407
I NEED MORE, CRISTINA.
YOU KNOW?

31:48.407 --> 31:51.490
I JUST CAN'T KEEP...

31:51.490 --> 31:53.332
I JUST NEED MORE,
YOU KNOW --

31:53.332 --> 31:55.995
MORE FROM YOU,
MORE FROM US.

31:55.995 --> 31:58.337
ANOTHER, PLEASE?
Bartender: YOU GOT IT!

31:58.337 --> 31:59.999
OKAY, LET'S JUST
GET OUT OF HERE.

31:59.999 --> 32:01.210
NOPE.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

32:01.210 --> 32:02.711
LET'S GO HOME.
JUST SLEEP THIS OFF,

32:02.711 --> 32:04.843
AND LET'S TALK ABOUT IT
IN THE MORNING, CAN WE --

32:04.843 --> 32:07.136
[ Chuckling ]
WE DON'T HAVE A HOME, CRISTINA.

32:07.136 --> 32:10.389
I HAVE A TRAILER, AND YOU HAVE
A ROOM AT KAREV'S HOUSE.

32:10.389 --> 32:11.760
IT'S NOT...

32:14.393 --> 32:16.395
ANOTHER, PLEASE.
RIGHT UP!

32:22.321 --> 32:24.323
[ PEANUT CRACKS ]

32:27.987 --> 32:30.239
THERE YOU GO.
THANK YOU.

32:30.239 --> 32:32.411
OH! THERE'S TOO MANY.

32:32.411 --> 32:34.203
THE KIDS
OUTNUMBER THE ADULTS.

32:34.203 --> 32:36.915
SHOULD'VE THOUGHT OF THAT
BEFORE WE ADOPTED AGAIN.

32:36.915 --> 32:39.958
I MEAN, WHAT IF THERE'S
A MUTINY? DEREK AND I WILL LOSE.

32:39.958 --> 32:42.171
NO, NOT UNTIL THE THIRD ONE
CAN WALK.

32:44.043 --> 32:46.045
SO, YOU BROKE UP AGAIN?

32:48.757 --> 32:52.391
SAME THING,
OVER AND OVER.

32:55.764 --> 32:59.518
YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE
IS THE SAME?

32:59.518 --> 33:00.689
THIS.

33:02.191 --> 33:06.405
YOU AND I LAYING IN THIS BED,
TALKING ABOUT YOU AND OWEN.

33:06.405 --> 33:08.777
WHY DO YOU KEEP DOING THIS
TO YOURSELF?

33:12.661 --> 33:14.663
[ Voice breaking ]
I NEED HELP.

33:19.328 --> 33:20.499
MER, YOU HAVE TO HELP ME.

33:20.499 --> 33:23.672
DON'T LET ME
GO BACK TO HIM --

33:23.672 --> 33:26.545
FOR HIS GOOD AND MINE.

33:26.545 --> 33:28.217
PLEASE HELP ME.

33:28.217 --> 33:31.430
OF COURSE.
OF COURSE I'LL HELP YOU.

33:37.896 --> 33:40.059
WHAT DO YOU MEAN? IT'S BEEN SIX
MONTHS SINCE MY LAST PROCEDURE!

33:40.059 --> 33:41.400
YOUR HAND'S STILL NOT HEALED!

33:41.400 --> 33:44.193
YOU NEED MORE P.T.
AND MORE TIME IN THE SKILLS LAB.

33:44.193 --> 33:46.445
YOU ARE NOT STEPPING
INTO THAT O.R. --

33:46.445 --> 33:47.906
NOT TODAY, MAYBE NOT EVER!

33:47.906 --> 33:49.698
ALL RIGHT, FIRST OF ALL,
YOU NEED TO LOWER YOUR VOICE.

33:49.698 --> 33:51.410
[ Laughing ] OH, OKAY! SO, WHAT,
NOBODY CAN YELL AT YOU?

33:51.410 --> 33:53.532
WHY'S THAT? WHY IS THAT?!
BECAUSE YOU'RE AN AVERY?
EXCUSE --

33:53.532 --> 33:56.325
THAT HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH ANY OF THIS, AND YOU --
SOME PAMPERED LITTLE RICH BOY

33:56.325 --> 33:58.036
WHO WAS GIFTED A HOSPITAL...
OH!

33:58.036 --> 34:00.079
...SO HE THINKS
THAT IT'S OKAY TO GO AHEAD

34:00.079 --> 34:02.921
AND ENDANGER PATIENTS, 'CAUSE
HE'S TOO DAMN PROUD TO ADMIT

34:02.921 --> 34:04.423
THAT HE CAN'T
OPERATE ANYMORE!

34:04.423 --> 34:05.464
DR. HUNT!

34:15.884 --> 34:19.808
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY INFANTS ARE
BORN WITHOUT A PULMONARY ARTERY?

34:19.808 --> 34:20.979
CRISTINA, I'M SO SORRY.

34:20.979 --> 34:22.811
BUT THERE IS A SURGERY
TO CORRECT IT.

34:22.811 --> 34:24.233
IT'S CALLED UNIFOCALIZATION,

34:24.233 --> 34:26.945
WHICH I WAS DOING
WITH A ROBOT.

34:26.945 --> 34:28.277
BUT NOW SHANE IS FINISHING IT

34:28.277 --> 34:30.279
BECAUSE YOU PAGED ME "911"
LIKE A MILLION TIMES.

34:30.279 --> 34:32.361
SO WHATEVER IT IS,
IT BETTER BE --
IT'S OWEN.

34:32.361 --> 34:34.783
HE WANTED TO WORK A SHIFT.
I DIDN'T FEEL COMFORTABLE.

34:34.783 --> 34:37.906
HE ONLY AGREED TO GET IN A BED
IF I PAGED YOU.

34:37.906 --> 34:40.659
[ SIGHS ]
YOU CAME.

34:42.961 --> 34:44.833
GIVE US A MINUTE.

34:49.208 --> 34:52.341
[ GRUNTS ]

34:52.341 --> 34:54.343
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!

34:54.343 --> 34:56.215
OH, GOD, YOU STINK.

34:56.215 --> 34:58.096
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:58.096 --> 35:00.098
YOU TRIED TO START A SHIFT?

35:00.098 --> 35:02.561
ARE YOU INSANE?
YOU COULD'VE HURT SOMEONE.

35:02.561 --> 35:06.225
YEAH. YEAH.
I LOVE YOU.

35:06.225 --> 35:09.818
THIS HAS GOT TO STOP.
I LOVE YOU.

35:09.818 --> 35:13.232
I LOVE YOU.
I LOVE YOU, AND, UH...

35:13.232 --> 35:15.654
I-I SEE YOU EVERY DAY,

35:15.654 --> 35:17.446
AND I CAN'T HAVE YOU.
[ SIGHS ]

35:17.446 --> 35:19.368
SO --
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

35:19.368 --> 35:22.371
SO HOW AM I SUPPOSED
TO KEEP DOING THIS,

35:22.371 --> 35:24.453
KEEP WORKING HERE, WHEN...

35:24.453 --> 35:26.835
EVERY TIME I TURN AROUND...

35:29.798 --> 35:30.959
...I SEE YOUR FACE.

35:30.959 --> 35:32.801
OWEN...

35:34.213 --> 35:35.594
OWEN, OWEN, OWEN, OWEN...

35:35.594 --> 35:38.136
I LOVE YOU.
PLEASE. PLEASE.

35:38.136 --> 35:40.759
PLEASE MARRY ME.
JUST MARRY ME.

35:40.759 --> 35:43.392
OWEN --
WHY CAN'T YOU JUST MARRY ME?

35:43.392 --> 35:46.265
PLEASE, I'M BEGGING YOU.
I'M BEGGING.

35:46.265 --> 35:47.476
I AM BEGGING YOU.

35:47.476 --> 35:49.938
I MEAN, WE SHOULD NEVER
HAVE CALLED IT QUITS.

35:49.938 --> 35:54.443
WE SHOULD NEVER HAVE CALLED IT
QUITS WHEN WE DID. PLEASE.
SHH, SHH, SHH, SHH.

35:56.655 --> 35:57.826
[ SNIFFLES ]

35:57.826 --> 36:00.369
[ SIGHS ]
JUST...

36:00.369 --> 36:02.331
[ SIGHS ]
PLEASE MARRY ME.

36:08.457 --> 36:10.459
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

36:13.922 --> 36:15.384
WELL, THERE'S NO SIGN
OF HIM YET,

36:15.384 --> 36:17.055
BUT THERE'S STILL PLENTY
OF TIME,

36:17.055 --> 36:18.387
SO THERE'S NO REASON
TO PANIC.

36:18.387 --> 36:20.008
I'M NOT PANICKED.
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY.

36:20.008 --> 36:22.010
CAN YOU GET MY BELT?
SURE.

36:24.062 --> 36:27.015
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

36:27.015 --> 36:28.607
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

36:28.607 --> 36:30.068
[ SIGHS ]
THANKS.

36:30.068 --> 36:31.109
HE IS LATE.

36:31.109 --> 36:33.191
HOW COULD HE
BE LATE TO THIS?

36:33.191 --> 36:35.193
I'LL GO LOOK FOR HIM AGAIN.

36:40.028 --> 36:41.700
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

36:41.700 --> 36:43.992
Owen: OKAY, WE'VE GOT
A FULL HOUSE, PEOPLE.
[ SIREN WAILING ]

36:43.992 --> 36:45.704
PAGE -- PAGE ANYONE
WHO'S AVAILABLE.
YES, SIR.

36:45.704 --> 36:47.376
WATCH YOUR BACK.
10-YEAR-OLD FEMALE
THROWN FROM A VEHICLE.

36:47.376 --> 36:49.418
MULTIPLE BLUNT INJURIES
AND HYPOTENSIVE.

36:49.418 --> 36:52.130
HEY, YOU -- ASSESS HER,
THEN RUSH HER UP TO RADIOLOGY

36:52.130 --> 36:54.883
GET A C.T. WITH CONTRAST.
UH-HUH.

36:54.883 --> 36:57.045
THEN PAGE ME AS SOON AS --
UM, EXCUSE ME.

36:57.045 --> 36:58.597
UM, CONTRAST,
LIKE THE IODINE DYE?
YEAH.

36:58.597 --> 37:00.509
I'M ALLERGIC TO THAT. DO YOU
THINK MY DAUGHTER COULD BE, TOO?

37:00.509 --> 37:03.302
WE'LL RUN A TEST AND CHECK.
NOT A PROBLEM. EXCUSE ME.

37:03.302 --> 37:05.143
WHAT'VE YOU GOT?

37:11.189 --> 37:13.442
Meredith: DO YOU WANT ME
TO CALL HIM AGAIN?

37:13.442 --> 37:14.693
NO.

37:14.693 --> 37:17.065
[ CELLPHONE BEEPING ]

37:24.913 --> 37:26.625
[ CELLPHONE BEEPING ]

37:26.625 --> 37:29.037
[ SIGHS ]
DO YOU HAVE TO TAKE THAT?

37:29.037 --> 37:31.920
'CAUSE YOU CAN GO.
IT -- IT'S NOT LIKE

37:31.920 --> 37:35.043
YOU HAVEN'T BEEN THROUGH THIS
WITH ME BEFORE.

37:35.043 --> 37:37.636
IT'S A GENERAL PAGE,
FOR WHOEVER'S ON CALL.

37:37.636 --> 37:40.639
I'M NOT EVEN ON CALL.
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

37:45.143 --> 37:46.885
WHAT HAPPENED?
[ MONITORS BEEPING LOUDLY ]

37:46.885 --> 37:48.477
SHE WAS SEIZING --
SEVERE ALLERGIC REACTION.

37:48.477 --> 37:51.269
I WAS PASSING BY AND SAW THIS
INTERN FREAKING OUT.

37:51.269 --> 37:52.771
I'VE GIVEN HER A .3 EPI.

37:52.771 --> 37:54.523
WELL,
DID ANYONE ORDER CONTRAST?

37:54.523 --> 37:55.564
WAS SHE TESTED FOR ALLERGIES?

37:55.564 --> 37:56.815
I GOT PAGED.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

37:56.815 --> 37:59.157
HEY. WE NEED TO GET HER
TO THE O.R. IMMEDIATELY.

37:59.157 --> 38:01.900
LET'S START HER ON BENADRYL
AND STEROIDS, STAT!

38:01.900 --> 38:03.322
IS THIS YOUR PATIENT?
YES.

38:03.322 --> 38:05.664
WHY DIDN'T YOU SCREEN HER
FOR ANY CONTRAST ALLERGIES?

38:05.664 --> 38:06.745
I DID.
IT'S NOT HERE.

38:06.745 --> 38:08.116
I MEAN, THERE'S NO RECORD
OF ANY TESTS.

38:08.116 --> 38:08.997
I ORDERED IT.
YOU DID?

38:08.997 --> 38:09.788
YES!
YOU SURE?

38:09.788 --> 38:11.169
YES.
YOU DID?

38:11.169 --> 38:14.082
HEY, I ORDERED THE DAMN TEST!

38:14.082 --> 38:15.123
DIDN'T I?

38:19.838 --> 38:22.130
CUTTING IT A LITTLE CLOSE,
DON'T YOU THINK?

38:22.130 --> 38:23.552
HI. SORRY I'M LATE.
I KNOW.

38:23.552 --> 38:25.844
I GOT HELD UP,
AND THERE WAS TRAFFIC AND --

38:25.844 --> 38:27.346
ANYWAY, SORRY.
I'M HERE NOW.

38:27.346 --> 38:29.808
YOU LOOK INCREDIBLE.

38:31.269 --> 38:32.601
THANK YOU.

38:32.601 --> 38:35.394
WELL...
SHALL WE DO THIS?

38:36.565 --> 38:38.567
LET'S.

38:38.567 --> 38:42.280
[ DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]

38:42.280 --> 38:44.282
THIS IS UNACCEPTABLE.

38:44.282 --> 38:46.034
THINGS LIKE THIS
KEEP HAPPENING,

38:46.034 --> 38:47.866
AND THIS TIME THERE
WAS A KID INVOLVED.

38:47.866 --> 38:49.998
AND I'M NOT LOOKING
THE OTHER WAY ANY LONGER.

38:49.998 --> 38:52.000
HE'S UNRELIABLE, A DANGER
TO HIS PATIENTS.

38:52.000 --> 38:53.161
I MEAN --
[ SCOFFS ]

38:53.161 --> 38:57.546
[ SIGHS ]
DID YOU SMELL HIS BREATH?

38:57.546 --> 38:59.418
YEAH, WELL, LET'S JUST WAIT
FOR THE BREATHALYZER RESULTS.

38:59.418 --> 39:02.421
NO. WE -- WE NEED TO CONVENE
AN EMERGENCY BOARD MEETING.

39:02.421 --> 39:04.843
[ SIGHS ]
RIGHT NOW, DEREK.
RIGHT NOW.

39:04.843 --> 39:08.346
SHE'S A PIONEER,
AN INSPIRATION, A MENTOR,

39:08.346 --> 39:12.601
AND, I'M PROUD TO SAY,
MY FRIEND FOR OVER 15 YEARS.

39:12.601 --> 39:13.852
PLEASE WELCOME,

39:13.852 --> 39:16.435
FOR AN UNPRECEDENTED
FOURTH CONSECUTIVE YEAR,

